<subSubSection id="E8EED39BFFD0EE04FF57FECFFF7CD376" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A04B8010FFD0EE04FF57FECFFF7CD376" blockId="5.[151,1436,261,540]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis id="92805C02FFD0EE04FF57FECFFEAFD002" bold="true" box="[199,314,333,360]" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The 
<taxonomicName id="67F4FB93FFD0EE04FEEBFECFFE56D00D" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[379,451,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis id="92805C02FFD0EE04FEEBFECFFE56D00D" box="[379,451,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is characterized by the following combination of characters: scutellum tridentate with median tooth longer than the lateral ones (Figs 61–70); elytra with uniform pattern of vestiture (
<figureCitation id="38CF9C95FFD0EE04FB7DFEF3FAF4D0E1" box="[1261,1377,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1656,1681]" captionTargetBox="[165,1418,186,1629]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1637]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Dorsal, group dispar: 9. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 10. A. dispar, 11. A. insuturatus, 12. A. schwarzi, 13. A. taeniopygus and 14. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557875" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557875/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">Figs 9–14</figureCitation>
); and pygidium with dense median strip of setae (
<figureCitation id="38CF9C95FFD0EE04FDEEFE17FC95D0C5" box="[638,768,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–83" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1746,1771]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,184,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,174,1727]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 78–83. Pygidium, group dispar: 78. Amblycerus crassipunctatus, 79. A. dispar, 80. A. insuturatus, 81. A. schwarzi, 82. A. taeniopygus and 83. Amblycerus goianiensis Santos &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, sp. n. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557901/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">Figs 78–83</figureCitation>
). It can be separated from the 
<taxonomicName id="67F4FB93FFD0EE04FBDFFE17FB21D0C5" authorityName="Kingsolver" authorityYear="1980" box="[1103,1204,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spondiae">
<emphasis id="92805C02FFD0EE04FBDFFE17FB21D0C5" box="[1103,1204,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">spondiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group mainly by the elytra with uniform pattern of vestiture (vertical stripes of setae, 
<taxonomicName id="67F4FB93FFD0EE04FCFBFE3BFC45D0B9" authorityName="Kingsolver" authorityYear="1980" box="[875,976,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spondiae">
<emphasis id="92805C02FFD0EE04FCFBFE3BFC45D0B9" box="[875,976,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">spondiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) and internal sac of male genitalia with different number and form of sclerites (two pairs and one unpaired sclerite with similar form, in the 
<taxonomicName id="67F4FB93FFD0EE04FAA7FE5FFA09D09D" authorityName="Kingsolver" authorityYear="1980" box="[1335,1436,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Amblycerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spondiae">
<emphasis id="92805C02FFD0EE04FAA7FE5FFA09D09D" box="[1335,1436,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="106">spondiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group).
</paragraph>
